7. HD / BIP32 Derivation as Deterministic Routing

HD derivation is used not as wallet logic but as state and authorization routing.


---

7.1 Global Context

const NETWORK_CONTEXT = H(canonicalize({
  environment: "production",
  domain: "deterministic-storage",
  protocol: "LCCP"
}));


---

7.2 Derivation Path

m / context / storage_a / storage_b / request_id / state


---

7.3 Example

m / H(context) / H(STORAGE_A_ID) / H(STORAGE_B_ID) / H(REQUEST_HASH) / 0  -> REQUEST
m / H(context) / H(STORAGE_A_ID) / H(STORAGE_B_ID) / H(REQUEST_HASH) / 1  -> OK
m / H(context) / H(STORAGE_A_ID) / H(STORAGE_B_ID) / H(REQUEST_HASH) / 2  -> RESPONSE

Rule

The derived path is a deterministic session index. It is not semantically interpreted; only structurally verified.


