10. Canonical Callback Table

The mempool acts as a pure execution router.

const EXECUTION_TABLE: Record<string, (request: any) => any> = {
  [H("REQUEST_HELLO")]: (request) => ({
    type: "HELLO_WORLD",
    payload: "HELLO_WORLD",
    request_hash: H(request),
    status: "EXECUTED"
  })
};

Rule

The mempool does not interpret full message semantics. It only verifies:

request type hash

authorized identity hash

context hash

canonical structure hash



